Falcon 500, talon FX provide options for current limit on both the supply and the stator. Stator when I measure is always higher.

Trying to protect both the motor and other mechanical component. Aluminum hex shaft sheared by two falcons 64:1 planetary and then 2:1 chain sprocket.

IMG_20220325_230724_013072×4080 2.36 MB

Which is the better current limit to use and why please?

Thanks.

Current Limiting TalonFX values Programming
The two current measurements are fundamentally different. The supply (input) current measurement is the value most people are familiar with, since that’s what was measured by Talon SRX. It’s the value of the current being drawn at the input bus voltage (which matches the current drawn through the PDP channel). The stator (output) current is a measure of the current being drawn by the motor, which is usually at a different voltage (whenever you’re not at 100% output). Since power in has to eq…
